cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and understanding of arithmetic word problems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper presents a novel approach to automatically solving arithmetic word problems using machine learning techniques. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning algorithms to develop a theory for expression trees and classifiers. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of image-based arithmetic word problems in their experiments. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the use of expression trees to represent and evaluate arithmetic expressions.
